, France":"Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France","Roye, Somme, Picardy, France":"Roye, Somme, Picardie, France","Roye, Somme, Picardie, França":"Roye, Somme, Picardie, France","Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, França":"Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hangest","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Upper or Lower Hergest (Herefordshire), a placename of uncertain etymology."],"variants":[{"name":"Hargis","meanings":["English (Essex): perhaps a variant of   Hargest  . Alternatively, an altered form of German or Frisian <b>Harges</b>, which is probably of the same origin as Frisian   Harjes  .","History: The (majority of the) American bearers of the surname <i>Hargis</i> trace their origin to George Hargis, who was transported from England to VA in 1642 and whose grandfather is believed by some to be Louis Harges, a Frenchman from Normandy, supposedly of Danish parentage. The surname <i>Harges</i> is not found neither in France nor in Denmark; it is, however, found in northern Germany, though it is very rare there."]}]},{"name":"Constance","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval form of the Late Latin name <i>Constantia</i>, which is either a feminine derivative of <i>Constans</i> (  see  Constant  ) or an abstract noun meaning ‘constancy’. This was a popular name among the Normans, and was borne by, amongst others, the formidable Constance of Sicily (  1158–98 ), wife of the Emperor  Henry VI ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Constance de Hangest was born in 1109, in Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France, her father, Ecuyer Roland de Hangest, was 31 and her mother, Hortense de Rosières, was 18. She married Ecuyer Henri de Roye in 1126. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1163, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1109–1163":"1109–1163","1108–1159":"1108–1159","1114–1169":"1114–1169","1104–1157":"1104–1157","1125–1182":"1125–1182","1138–1193":"1138–1193","1078–1163":"1078–1163","1091–1142":"1091–1142","1091":"1091","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1138":"1138","1126":"1126","de 1129 a 1163":"1129 kuni 1163","1104":"1104","1159":"1159","1125":"1125","1169":"1169","1114":"1114","1157":"1157","1078":"1078","1109":"1109","1108":"1108","Hangest-en-Santerre, France":"Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Roye, Somme, Picardy, France":"Roye, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Roye, Somme, Picardie, França":"Roye, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, França":"Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1109–1163":"1109–1163","1108–1159":"1108–1159","1114–1169":"1114–1169","1104–1157":"1104–1157","1125–1182":"1125–1182","1138–1193":"1138–1193","1078–1163":"1078–1163","1091–1142":"1091–1142","1091":"1091","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1138":"1138","1126":"1126","de 1129 a 1163":"vuodesta 1129 vuoteen 1163","1104":"1104","1159":"1159","1125":"1125","1169":"1169","1114":"1114","1157":"1157","1078":"1078","1109":"1109","1108":"1108","Hangest-en-Santerre, France":"Hangest-en-Santerre, Somme, Pic